ce:section.ce:para:
Numerous reports were considerably interested in studying the superior biological activities of CQDs-based polysaccharides represented in antimicrobial, anticancer and antiviral activities (Fig. 4
                        ). Moreover, their mechanism of action was simply hypothesized and approved according to literature (Fig. 5
                        ). CQDs were differently reported to exhibit excellent antimicrobial activity against different pathogens, such as Escherichia coli, Bacillus cereus, Candida albicans. Whereas, the estimated minimal inhibitory concentration (MIC) for CQDs ingrained from guar gum was 350–450 μL/mL (Ahmed & Emam, 2020). CQDs ingrained from MCC also showed excellent microbicidal action and MIC was located in the range of 100–350 μg/mL against Bacillus cereus & Escherichia coli and 300–400 μg/mL against Candida albicans (Mogharbel et al., 2023). Moreover, the effect of doping AgNPs within CQDs that were nucleated from β-cyclodextrin, was showed with superior antimicrobial action, as the cell viability percentage was estimated for Staphylococcus aureus, Escherichia coli and Candida albicans after incubation with quantum dots to be 0.0–0.1 % (Almahri et al., 2023).
